Quote: A Nelson company is recruiting 60 workers from Asia to crew its domestic fishing boats... The Maritime Union yesterday condemned the plans to recruit foreign workers as "sweatship labour". General Secretary Trevor Hanson said the maritime industry was being "ripped apart" by the use of "sweatships" off the New Zealand coast.
